                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1396">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">702.0093/11–2549: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Peiping</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Clubb</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-25T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >November 25, 1949—noon.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received November 25—2:29 a. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2080. Consuls yesterday decided send letter (Contel 2054, November 23 [<hi
                        rend="italic">22</hi>]) Land Bureau tomorrow along indicated lines without
                    title, unless in receipt prior contrary instructions. French Consul for present
                    unable act in view instruction from his office Shanghai.</p>
                <p>Sent Department 2080; department pass Nanking 1175, Tientsin 101, Shanghai
                    1215.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Clubb</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
